cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a novel on-line visual tracking framework based on deep learning techniques, specifically the Siamese matching network and meta-learner network. The paper focuses on computer vision and machine learning, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) category. Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques and meta-learning suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. The tracking aspect of the paper suggests that it could also belong to the cs.RO (Robotics) category, as visual tracking is an important aspect of robotics. Finally, the use of real-time speeds suggests that it could also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) category, as real-time processing is important in multimedia applications.
